<br>
Vick reached into his pocket and produced a cell phone. He triggered the direct connect. &quot;Ross, what's your '20?&quot;<br>
<br>
His partner answered with indecipherable static.<br>
<br>
Deuce shrugged at Vick as he gave him a quizzical look.<br>
<br>
&quot;They're tearing this town apart! What the hell are they doing, here?&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce bit down on his lip. He could taste blood. Must have gotten his block chopped somewhere back there.  &quot;They're looking for something.&quot;<br>
<br>
Vick tried his partner again, but got no response.<br>
<br>
&quot;Where do you think they all are?&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce called out over another blast of energy in the distance, &quot;I can't think with this racket! Let's get out of the weather!&quot;<br>
<br>
He led Vick around a shattered concrete fountain, high-stepping through deepening puddles. They splashed across the courtyard towards an anonymous official building. With a wide swipe of the butt of his Browning, Deuce opened up the glass of the front door, and they stepped inside.<br>
<br>
Rainwater dripped from Deuce's bangs in a stream. His ears were still ringing. Permanent hearing loss.<br>
<br>
&quot;Bastards.&quot;<br>
<br>
Vick screwed his brows together. &quot;What?&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce gestured his thumb back out the door. &quot;Think your partner's still alive?&quot;<br>
<br>
Vick shrugged. &quot;Probably quivering under a desk somewhere.&quot; He maintained his gaze. &quot;What are YOU doing here, anyway?&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce snarled. &quot;Trying not to get my ass blown off!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You know what I mean. You're not FBI. At least, not anymore.&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce tensed his shoulders, and lifted his stare slowly up to Vick. It was his warning sign... but Vick wasn't budging.<br>
<br>
&quot;This means you are?&quot;<br>
<br>
Vick shrugged innocently.<br>
<br>
Deuce sighed. &quot;Who's your A.D.?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Morgan.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Jesus, he made Assistant? Ass kisser. He couldn't find his dick if he had to take a leak.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;How long have you been out of the circuit?&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce released his clip and fished through his pockets for ammo. &quot;Five years come November.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What happened? What turned you?&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce found a full clip's worth of rounds and began to plug them into the clip.  &quot;When one of your operatives risks his neck to protect your reputation and your job, you just don't send him up the river without an explanation. You just... don't. Anyway, the bureau's got this thing against vendetta.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;So you're working for the mafia? The Arabs? CIA?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Little bit of each. Whoever signs the paychecks, you know? Actually, I still turn some tricks for the Bureau. Morgan may be as straight as you lace them, but A.D. Cocker isn't above alternative methods.&quot;<br>
<br>
Vick smirked. &quot;Morgan's not so straight-laced. He's the one who's opened us up to psychic testimony.&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce froze. &quot;...Liz. You're here for Liz.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;She's a primary witness to the Chapin murders.&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce nodded, clapped his clip, and slid it into the Browning.<br>
<br>
Vick continued, &quot;You said these aliens were looking for something. What if they're looking for Liz, too?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Why would they?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, if she's a psychic... and if they're psychic... maybe she's picking up on their thoughts.&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce winced. &quot;Pretty thin.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, what about you? What's your interest in the girl?&quot;<br>
<br>
He shrugged. &quot;I don't know. No agenda. Unlike you and our friends up there...&quot; He sniffed. &quot;She's kind of cute, kind of dangerous... my kind of girl.&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce chambered a round, pulled back the hammer and jammed the barrel at Vick's forehead.<br>
<br>
Vick returned a cold stare. &quot;The hell?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You're in possession of more information than I'm comfortable with. So, when this is over, and we're all still alive... I want you to remember...&quot;  Deuce gently slid the hammer back and lowered the gun. &quot;...I could have killed you.&quot;<br>
<br>
Vick exhaled. The cell phone in his pocket chirped.<br>
<br>
He thumbed the direct connect. &quot;Ross?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Vick! You're not going to believe this...&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uazoth30k.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azoth30k</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/29/01 12:24:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=69>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Another player!</span><hr size=1> ((Just finished reading this and figured I might get in on the action... If you don't mind of course))<br>
<br>
Across the street from the front of the police building and the saucer a lone figure was hunched against the wall of a store trying to avoid as much of the storm as possible. He was tall, probably six foot six if you had to guess, and firmly built with short cropped silver hair. His eyes never left the saucer as he reached into his trench coat and removed a small ovoid device. With a faint beep the ovoid split in two with a faintly glowing rectangle between the halves.<br>
<br>
&quot;Graydon, you there?&quot; He called glancing at the com unit, &quot;We have a bit of a problem down here.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;What? Az, what kind of a problem do we have?&quot; A slightly annoyed voice came from the device accompanied by the image of a man in his early thirties.<br>
<br>
Keeping his eyes on the saucer Azoth quietly reported, &quot;We have at least one saucer... I think they're Greys... that I've visually confirmed. I think they're after something here, they're not just grabbing people like they usually do. They're hunting.&quot;<br>
<br>
Graydon got a puzzled expression on his face. &quot;How do you know they're hunting?&quot; He received a look from Azoth for that. &quot;Right, I know, you're a hunter too. You recognise these things. Blah blah blah.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Exactly.&quot; Replied Az with a grin, &quot;I'm moving in.&quot; He started out from his cover when a shout from the com stopped him in his tracks.<br>
<br>
&quot;Wait! What have you got on you?&quot; Graydon queried.<br>
<br>
With a faint smile Az went down the list of equipment he was carrying, &quot;Let's see... I have my AGS-356 anti-mech pistol with three rounds, but I doubt I'm going to find any cymechs down here, then there's my twin KKV-3 plasmas with eighty rounds each, my GN-5 holdout with twenty rounds, a WSTE-M5 combat shotgun with five rounds, four fusion grenades, my monosaber, and twelve small throwing knives. That's about it.&quot;<br>
<br>
It was a moment before Graydon replied with a quiet &quot;oh.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;That's right, I've got my mask too,&quot; Az ammended, &quot;so I sould be good to go&quot; So saying he slipped an obsidian mask marked with twin slashes of red onto his face. When it locked down with a faint hiss the eyes lit up into a faint red. <br>
<br>
Putting the com unit back into his pocket he slipped out into the thrashing wind and rain. They didn't bother him much, the wind and rain that is, both were much worse where he had spent most of his early life. He had headed back behind the store that was his cover. It wouldn't do for the aliens to see him coming. <br>
<br>
Circling around the squat building he headed across the occupied street at the next intersection. Now he was on the same side of the street as the police building and, fortunately, the aliens. <br>
<br>
Ducking and weaving around both garbage cans and dumpsters that had been thrown around in the storm Azoth came upon the Police building. The discharge of alien weaponry was growing louder in the distance. Sparing a quick glance for the street that intersected the alley he was in Azoth stopped dead in his tracks. <br>
<br>
&quot;Maybe I will need the 356&quot; He said to himself. For standing there in the street was a decently sized mech. There were also three people by said mech; one was doing a decent impression of an unconscious human while the other two were looking at each other in shock. They didn't notice the three aliens, no they weren't Greys, sneaking up on them around the legs of the mech. <br>
<br>
They didn't, but Azoth did.<br>
<br>
Unholstering his KKV's Azoth clicked the safeties off on the plasma pistols. Thinking twice he deactivated the laser sights, they wouldn't be needed with his mask. The aliens didn't pay any attention to him, they were focused on something else... The girl. They were all headed for the girl. <br>
<br>
Stepping away from his cover Azoth let the lead one have it in the chest with two plasma bolts. One down. The girl and her friend snapped out of their trance at the sound of the weapons fire and headed for cover. The second plasma pistol spoke and a second alien dropped. Two down. The third managed to level some kind of weapon at its attacker. With a clap of thunder a bolt of electricity connected Azoth and the alien. For Azoth, time stopped, everything went black and then there was a strange sensation of flying. Of course he wasn't paying too much attention to that, the searing pain in his chest was where he was focusing most of his awareness. A jarring thump followed, though he didn't feel it much, and there was still no light. <br>
<br>
It took several seconds for the mask to reboot, it had never crashed before, so for those precious seconds his world remained dark. His mind was muddled, he wasn't sure who he was but he knew that he was in danger. He had to get up. But he couldn't see anything and then there was that ringing. With the snap of a flash the world returned to him. The rain was sleeting down leaving large drops on his field of view. Then Azoth's memory returned. With a gasp he sat up, realised that he was at least thirty feet from his previous position, and looked for the last alien.<br>
<br>
It wasn't hard to find. In fact it was standing there out in the open approaching the girl. It was ignoring him and the man the girl was with, it didn't consider them a threat. That was a mistake. It was while Azoth was leveling his one remaining plasma pistol, he must have dropped the other, at the alien that something truly remarkable happened. The alien took to the air in what was a very similar flight to the one that Azoth had just taken. Shrugging inwardly he shot it out of the air, it didn't matter much if it was moving or not, a target's a target. It landed on the ground in a crumpled smoking heap.<br>
<br>
Finding and picking up his other pistol, Azoth wearily made his way over to the man and girl.<br>
<br>
&quot;I suggest we get out of here,&quot; he gasped, noticing for the first time that he was short of breath, &quot;there are probably more of them...&quot;<br>
<br>
